{"title_page": "C. R. Srinivasan", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=July 2018}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name        = C. R. Srinivasan\n| image       =\n| image_size  = 200px\n| caption     = \n| birth_name  = \n| birth_date  = {{Birth date|df=yes|1889|11|28}}\n| birth_place = \n| death_date  = {{Death date and age|df=yes|1962|01|29|1889|11|28}}\n| death_place = [[Madras]], [[India]]\n| death_cause = \n| resting_place =\n| resting_place_coordinates = \n| residence   = \n| nationality = \n| other_names = \n| known_for   = journalism, banking expertise\n| education   = \n| employer    = \n| occupation  = journalist\n| title       = \n| height      = \n| weight      = \n| spouse      = \n| children    = [[C. S. Narasimhan]]\n| signature   = \n| website     = \n| footnotes   = \n}}\n\n'''C. R. Srinivasan''' (28 November 1889 \u2013 29 January 1962) was an Indian journalist who served as [[Managing Director]] of the Tamil language newspaper ''[[Swadesamitran]]'' from 1934 to 1962.\n\n== Early career ==\n\nBorn on 28 November 1889,<ref name=\"rangap290\">{{cite book | title=About Bygone Cherished Days: Life, Times, and Work of Dewan Bahadur S. Srinivasa Raghavaiyangar, C.I.E., and Other Distinguished Personalities| last=Raghavan| first=K. Ranga|author2=Seshayangar Srinivasa Raghavaiyangar| year=1993| publisher=Pankajam R. Raghavan|page=290}}</ref> Srinivasan graduated from the [[Presidency College, Madras]] in 1910 and joined ''Swadesamitran'', a newspaper run by his maternal uncle, [[A. Rangaswami Iyengar]] as Manager and Assistant Editor in 1915.<ref name=\"nairp152\">{{cite book|title=Peeps at the press in South India: a short survey of the achievements of editors and publishers|page=152|first=A. A.|last=Nair|year=1966}}</ref> When Rangaswami Iyengar moved over to ''[[The Hindu]]'' in 1928, Srinivasan became the editor of the newspaper.<ref name=\"nairp152\" /> He also became the Managing Director in 1934.<ref name=\"nairp152\" />\n\n== Death ==\n\nSrinivasan died on 29 January 1962 at the age of seventy-two.<ref name=\"rangap290\" /><ref name=\"gyanp523\">{{cite book|title=Land and people of Indian states and union territories. 25. Tamil Nadu|page=523|chapter=Important Events}}</ref> He was succeeded as Managing Director by his son, [[C. S. Narasimhan]].\n\n== Notes ==\n\n{{reflist}}\n\n== References ==\n\n* {{cite news|title=The beginning of Tamil journalism|first=S.|last=Muthiah|authorlink=S. Muthiah|date=23 July 2003|url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/mp/2003/07/23/stories/2003072300090200.htm|work=[[The Hindu]]}}\n* {{cite news|title=This Day That Age: C. R. Srinivasan passes away|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-miscellaneous/article2843578.ece|work=The Hindu|date=30 January 2012}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Srinivasan, C. R.}}\n[[Category:1889 births]]\n[[Category:1962 deaths]]\n[[Category:Presidency College, Chennai alumni]]\n[[Category:Indian newspaper editors]]\n[[Category:Writers from Chennai]]\n[[Category:Indian male journalists]]\n[[Category:20th-century Indian journalists]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=July 2018}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name        = C. R. Srinivasan\n| image       =\n| image_size  = 200px\n| caption     = \n| birth_name  = \n| birth_date  = {{Birth date|df=yes|1889|11|28}}\n| birth_place = \n| death_date  = {{Death date and age|df=yes|1962|01|29|1889|11|28}}\n| death_place = [[Madras]], [[India]]\n| death_cause = \n| resting_place =\n| resting_place_coordinates = \n| residence   = \n| nationality = \n| other_names = \n| known_for   = journalism, banking expertise\n| education   = \n| employer    = \n| occupation  = journalist\n| title       = \n| height      = \n| weight      = \n| spouse      = \n| children    = [[C. S. Narasimhan]]\n| signature   = \n| website     = \n| footnotes   = \n}}\n\n'''C. R. Srinivasan''' (28 November 1889 \u2013 29 January 1962) was an Indian journalist who served as [[Managing Director]] of the Tamil language newspaper ''[[Swadesamitran]]'' from 1934 to 1962.\n\n== Early career ==\n\nBorn on 28 November 1889,<ref name=\"rangap290\">{{cite book | title=About Bygone Cherished Days: Life, Times, and Work of Dewan Bahadur S. Srinivasa Raghavaiyangar, C.I.E., and Other Distinguished Personalities| last=Raghavan| first=K. Ranga|author2=Seshayangar Srinivasa Raghavaiyangar| year=1993| publisher=Pankajam R. Raghavan|page=290}}</ref> Srinivasan graduated from the [[Presidency College, Madras]] in 1910 and joined ''Swadesamitran'', a newspaper run by his maternal uncle, [[A. Rangaswami Iyengar]] as Manager and Assistant Editor in 1915.<ref name=\"nairp152\">{{cite book|title=Peeps at the press in South India: a short survey of the achievements of editors and publishers|page=152|first=A. A.|last=Nair|year=1966}}</ref> When Rangaswami Iyengar moved over to ''[[The Hindu]]'' in 1928, Srinivasan became the editor of the newspaper.<ref name=\"nairp152\" /> He also became the Managing Director in 1934.<ref name=\"nairp152\" />\n\n== Death ==\n\nSrinivasan died on 29 January 1962 at the age of seventy-two.<ref name=\"rangap290\" /><ref name=\"gyanp523\">{{cite book|title=Land and people of Indian states and union territories. 25. Tamil Nadu|page=523|chapter=Important Events}}</ref> He was succeeded as Managing Director by his son, [[C. S. Narasimhan]].\n\n== Notes ==\n\n{{reflist}}\n\n== References ==\n\n* {{cite news|title=The beginning of Tamil journalism|first=S.|last=Muthiah|authorlink=S. Muthiah|date=23 July 2003|url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/mp/2003/07/23/stories/2003072300090200.htm|work=[[The Hindu]]}}\n* {{cite news|title=This Day That Age: C. R. Srinivasan passes away|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-miscellaneous/article2843578.ece|work=The Hindu|date=30 January 2012}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Srinivasan, C. R.}}\n[[Category:1889 births]]\n[[Category:1962 deaths]]\n[[Category:Presidency College, Chennai alumni]]\n[[Category:Indian newspaper editors]]\n[[Category:Writers from Chennai]]\n[[Category:Indian male journalists]]\n[[Category:20th-century Indian journalists]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/C._R._Srinivasan"}
